Totally agree on this point.<p>My feeling is that Rule 9 roughly maps to following the Law of Demeter in that you shouldn&#x27;t chase properties down more than one level, e.g.<p>Good:<p><pre><code>   var something = obj.property;
</code></pre>
Bad:<p><pre><code>   var something = obj.property1.property2.property3;</code></pre>
